    "final_message": "Two bugs fixed, all 6 tests pass:\n\n1. **`get` missing `move_to_end`** (`cache.py:30`) \u2014 reading a key didn't promote it to MRU position, so it could be evicted ahead of older items.\n2. **`put` evicting on updates** (`cache.py:33`) \u2014 the capacity check fired even when the key already existed, incorrectly evicting the LRU entry for a zero-net-size update. Fixed by adding `key not in self._data` to the guard.",
