    "final_message": "**Bug 1 (`get`, line 30):** `get` returned the value without calling `move_to_end`, so reads didn't update LRU order. A later `put` could evict an entry that had just been read.\n\n**Bug 2 (`put`, lines 32\u201334):** `put` checked capacity and evicted *before* checking whether the key already existed. Updating an existing key doesn't add a new entry, so eviction was incorrectly triggered. Fix: only evict when `key not in self._data` and the cache is full.",
